main event: Two bright white shaped objects were observed in the sky over San Jose, California on June 29, 1965.
interesting points: The objects were described as funnel-shaped and approximately the size of a basketball.
The objects were flying in line, very close together, and moving south.
Contrails were observed trailing the objects.
The objects were visible for approximately 3 minutes.
The observer was a civilian located at 462 Rennie Ave in San Jose, California.
result: Possible identification as aircraft or satellites, but final analysis impossible with the information provided.
photographs: Yes, but not included in the report
